{"id":6888,"date":"2024-01-19T14:26:10","date_gmt":"2020-03-19T08:56:10","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=6888"},"modified":"2024-08-28T15:53:12","modified_gmt":"2024-08-28T10:23:12","slug":"small-bathroom-design-ideas","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bathroom-interiors\/small-bathroom-design-ideas\/","title":{"rendered":"Wash Away Your Blues With These Bold Designs For Small Bathrooms"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p><em>Designing a bathroom can be challenging, but our ideas here will help you design the perfect bathroom regardless of space.&nbsp;<\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Worried that your bathroom won&#8217;t look good if you have a small home? Designing a small bathroom can be challenging. You will want to keep as many of your personal care essentials. And it is possible with a little creativity and planning. There are several aspects to keep in mind as you design a small bathroom. From creative storage options, smart finishes and some detailing, there is a basketful of ideas to make a small bathroom look extravagant. Here are a few of our top tricks to make your small bathroom look glamorous. <\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Mirrors Can Do Wonders<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Mirrors in a small bathroom elevate the style quotient threefolds and create the illusion of space. This is an age-old secret used by most interior designers. Double the look and feel of your bathroom with a mirror. It is especially useful if you have a narrow bathroom. Mirrors also reflect light and make your small bathroom nice and bright. See how this square shaped mirror framed in wood automatically gives you a feeling of space? Yes, that\u2019s what we are talking about! <\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013143\/small-bathroom-ideas-with-mirrors.jpg\" alt=\"Small bathroom ideas with light-reflecting mirrors to create a beautiful, bright space\" class=\"wp-image-6895\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013143\/small-bathroom-ideas-with-mirrors.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013143\/small-bathroom-ideas-with-mirrors-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013143\/small-bathroom-ideas-with-mirrors-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013143\/small-bathroom-ideas-with-mirrors-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Turn your small bathroom into a spacious zone with mirrors<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Wall Mounted Toilets Save Floor Space<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>If you have enough wall space in your bathroom a wall-mounted toilet tank can save both the floor space and legroom. This type of toilet hides plumbing related hardware because of the absence of a flush tank. Wall-mounted toilets instantly bring in sleek, clean aesthetics to small bathrooms. Also a floating commode leaves you room below to show off patterned tiles seamlessly. <\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013147\/small-bathroom-storage-ideas-home.jpg\" alt=\"Small bathroom design ideas with wall-mounted toilet tank to save floor space and legroom\" class=\"wp-image-6896\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013147\/small-bathroom-storage-ideas-home.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013147\/small-bathroom-storage-ideas-home-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013147\/small-bathroom-storage-ideas-home-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013147\/small-bathroom-storage-ideas-home-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A wall-mounted toilet is increasingly becoming popular because of its sleek, slender, space-saving design<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Why Only The Toilet, Your Sink Can Float Too<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>As with wall-mounted toilets, wall-mounted washbasins are an excellent way to save floor space to make your small bathroom look larger. If you need extra storage space, then a floating vanity trolley like the one in this image gives you a dedicated place to stack all your essential toiletries. A sink atop uses this side of the wall judiciously. It is easy for a small bathroom to look cluttered. Opt for flat panelled cabinets for its sleek and streamlined design.  <\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013128\/floating-sink-small-bathroom-design-ideas.jpg\" alt=\"Bathroom designs for small spaces featuring wall-mounted washbasins for a clutter-free look\" class=\"wp-image-6891\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013128\/floating-sink-small-bathroom-design-ideas.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013128\/floating-sink-small-bathroom-design-ideas-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013128\/floating-sink-small-bathroom-design-ideas-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013128\/floating-sink-small-bathroom-design-ideas-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">You can&#8217;t beat the functionality of a floating sink like this<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"941\" height=\"2877\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/22180130\/seven-decor-tips-for-small-bathrooms.jpg\" alt=\"Small bathroom decor tips: wall storage, mirrors, compact fixtures, layered lighting, open shelves, vertical and bold accents\" class=\"wp-image-58631\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/22180130\/seven-decor-tips-for-small-bathrooms.jpg 941w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/22180130\/seven-decor-tips-for-small-bathrooms-98x300.jpg 98w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/22180130\/seven-decor-tips-for-small-bathrooms-335x1024.jpg 335w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/22180130\/seven-decor-tips-for-small-bathrooms-768x2348.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/22180130\/seven-decor-tips-for-small-bathrooms-50x153.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/22180130\/seven-decor-tips-for-small-bathrooms-502x1536.jpg 502w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/22180130\/seven-decor-tips-for-small-bathrooms-670x2048.jpg 670w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/08\/22180130\/seven-decor-tips-for-small-bathrooms-150x459.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 941px) 100vw, 941px\" \/><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Small Bathroom Cabinets For Extra Storage<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Since the bathroom is where you clean and wash up, it only makes sense to make it the freshest space in your home. By this we mean clutter-free basins, neatly hung towels, and no water stains. Give everything a dedicated space \u2014 makeup, toiletries, dry towels, and more \u2014 with cabinets like this that are just right for a small bathroom. Choose a cabinet design built with multiple drawers, and cupboards to organise your things that are otherwise displayed on countertops.  <\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013131\/small-bathroom-cabinet-for-extra-storage.jpg\" alt=\"Small bathroom cabinet in blue colour\" class=\"wp-image-6892\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013131\/small-bathroom-cabinet-for-extra-storage.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013131\/small-bathroom-cabinet-for-extra-storage-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013131\/small-bathroom-cabinet-for-extra-storage-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013131\/small-bathroom-cabinet-for-extra-storage-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Organise your small bathroom with a multi-storage cabinet built under the sink<\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p>Also, check out&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bathroom-interiors\/bathroom-storage-ideas\/\">Creative Bathroom Storage Ideas<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Rip Of The Shower Curtain, Add A Glass Panel<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Let&#8217;s be honest here &#8211; nobody likes the idea of a shower curtain. Not only does it stick to your body during a shower they also lose their colour and sheen over time. Shower curtains also make bathrooms look smaller as it closes off one-third of the area visually. Swap your shower curtain with a lustrous glass panel to open up your bathroom and allow more light into your shower. Just make sure you avoid sliding glass panels that require bottom and top racks as they are hard to clean.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-image\">\n<figure class=\"aligncenter\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013140\/small-bathroom-designs-with-shower.jpg\" alt=\"Small bathroom designs with glass panel\" class=\"wp-image-6894\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013140\/small-bathroom-designs-with-shower.jpg 800w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013140\/small-bathroom-designs-with-shower-300x200.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013140\/small-bathroom-designs-with-shower-768x512.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/03\/21013140\/small-bathroom-designs-with-shower-150x100.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Glass panels will add volume to your space constraint in a bathroom <\/figcaption><\/figure><\/div>\n\n\n<p><strong>PRO TIPS<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Remove the bathtub as they take up twice the amount of space compared to standing showers<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bathtubs are pretty expensive and there is the extra cost of installation<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>If you need a bathtub for your kids then go for a low one as it makes getting in and&nbsp; out easier&nbsp;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Steal these small bathroom design ideas to give your space a complete makeover. Do not let a compact space be a barrier to your dream bathroom. As you can see the possibilities are endless to maximise the area and overall look of your bathroom. Let us know your suggestions in the comment section below.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Also, Check Out<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bathroom-interiors\/how-to-organise-your-bathroom\/\">Organise Your Bathroom the Marie Kondo Way<\/a><\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bathroom-interiors\/bathroom-cabinet-designs\/\">Bathroom Cabinet Designs<\/a><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Luxurious Modular Interior Design Ideas<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Design your personal oasis of comfort<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phone-ext\" id=\"id_select2_example\" class=\"id_select2_example drop-downfield form-dropdown\"\n                onfocus='this.size=5;' onblur='this.size=1;' onchange='this.size=1; this.blur();'\n                data-width=\"100%\" data-minimum-results-for-search=\"Infinity\">\n               \n                <option value=\"+01\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06163948\/01.png\">\n                    +01\n                <\/option>\n                <option value=\"+91\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06164015\/91.png\"\n                    selected>\n             